They can't afford to bend any more rules, and people who are new to the case won't bend any rules, for fear of ending up in the same situation. It's impossible to know for sure; perhaps someone, somewhere, with all the right connections, leverage, and know-how will find a discreet way of brushing this under the carpet. I doubt it, though. comment: This is a nothing burger.  It happened over 5 years ago and here in the US, that is past the statute of limitations and I am sure Australia is similar in their statute of limitations.  I retired from DHS/HSI as a Special Agent last summer and worked tons of these type of cases.  They are a non-issue, to be honest.  And I worked with the Australian Border Force on numerous occasions and they have MUCH bigger fish to fry than someone bringing their pets in and even if they lied about it, it's really not a huge deal.  And they won't lose their work visa or even be turned away on a visa waiver because they can easily get something like that fixed with an immigration attorney, if needed.  Trust me, when a kilo of coke goes for $20k here and it sells for $220K in Australia, there are a lot more important cases that they are focusing on.  I know, I worked them

comment:
Australia is very strict in border control...
i nearly got put behind bars under the ter ror ist act. 
I kid you not.
It showed up on scanning, that i had been exposed to "b o m b   making materials"...
Holy crap. 
Been in Oz 6 weeks...one last job to do before flying home...fertilize the lemon tree...
Urea/sheep poo fertilizer, stomped into ground with shoes...
darn, clean shoes off with nappy wipes.(trainers with deep grooves) 
 Wipe arms off with nappy wipe due to dry dust...just before very hot car drive to airport, grab sons spray deodorant, quick squirt under arms...!...
Through passport control then Alarm bells pinging everywhere and suddenly surrounded by uniformed men!....
questions, be prepared to get body searched, and upend bags in secure room...WTF...
Scared witless, but asked why detained...
Mumbles and excuses...
no, i had the right to know what im supposed to have done, or what the allegations were !
The combination of Urea, Glycerol (in nappy wipes) and alcohol in deodorant had triggered all sensors..
Upshot, very brown arms with white hands (garden gloves), everything taken home as presents legal and declared, bags tested, nothing on or in them that glowed...upshot, explanation accepted after extensive questioning about all wherabouts in the 6 weeks, and finally released to be running late for the plane...
Faffed if i know how AH wasnt detained for lying cos they dont muck around.
Scariest thing ive been through in an airport, and under that Act, you can be detained without legal representation while they sort it out
